The paper deals with the problem of multi-robot path planning, which involves coordinating the movements of multiple robots to achieve a common goal. This problem is a key area of research in the fields of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes two integer linear programming models for solving the problem, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graphs in the problem formulation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making it relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
